[normal]“The recent Ofsted experience was unjust and it was cl
[normal]ear to all involved that the result was pre-decided and that the inspectors were drawing conclusions about the school to fit historical data and meet the government agenda.  There is not a member of staff or parent at the school who agrees with the result 
[normal]given by Ofsted or what is said in the report.”
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]“It confirmed what I thought about Ofsted.  The criteria they judge a school on is so specific and focused on evidence provided by SLT
[normal] [senior leadership team]
[normal] that they do not notice anything else going on.
[normal]  This just encourages SLT to spend more time on Ofsted evidence and less time on running the school.  A sad state of affairs.  Ofsted serves no useful purpose to education and should be abolished.”
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]“We are due now and the pressure is so great it is makin
[normal]g me ill.  I am considering leaving because of it.”
